text: Niphadoses palleucus is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Ian Francis Bell Common in 1960. It is found in north-western Australia. Larvae have been recorded on cultivated rice.A revision of the Australian Stem Borers hitherto referred to Schoenobius and Scirpophaga (Lepidoptera: Pyralidae, Schoenobiinae) ==References== Category:Moths described in 1960 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Niphadoses palleucus
